This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Due to defendants compliance with the terms of the DPA, Court cancelled the midpoint review hearing. Court schedule the final review hearing with parties for February 7th, 2023 at 1:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Community Service hours
Received and Filed. MATC Firearm Course Certificate

Defendant Jasmine K Nash in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.
The defendant was advised of her constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions/elements and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the case transferred to Judge Stark, Branch 17 for a review hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Elements of the Offense, Received and Filed.
Deferred Prosecution Agreement, Received and Filed.
Addendum to Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Received and Filed.

Defendant Jasmine K Nash in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jasmine K Nash appeared by video means with Attorney. Attorney Flynn informed the Court that there is a DPA offer and requests additional time for defendant to schedule a TAD evaluation. Court ordered case adjourned for deferred prosecution agreement hearing in Branch 37. All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for August 18, 2022 at 09:30 am.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
 DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 5/20/22. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Defendant Jasmine K Nash in court.  Jennifer L Pickett appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 05/18/2022@2:00pm
